cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.HC

The paper focuses on the delivery of 360$^{\circ}$ video services and the potential value of caching-based techniques for bandwidth savings. This topic is relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). However, given the emphasis on video delivery and network optimization, cs.MM and cs.NI are the most likely categories. The paper also involves data analysis and prediction, which aligns with cs.CV and cs.DC. Finally, the study considers user behavior and experience, which relates to cs.HC.
